<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-24T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/668: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-24T10:00:00-05:00">July 24, 1931—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>73. Law and Order Cabinet headed by former Minister of the Interior
                            Frodden has taken charge of the situation. Disturbances continued
                            throughout the night but this morning city is quiet.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>